3пёЏвѓЈ Default OpenShift Behavior
Normally OpenShift allows all authenticated users to create projects.
Why?
Because of this ClusterRoleBinding:
self-provisioners
Check it:
oc describe clusterrolebinding self-provisioners
You will see:
subjects:
Group system:authenticated:oauth
Meaning:
Any logged-in user can run:
oc new-project myproject
________________________________________
4пёЏвѓЈ Restrict Project Creation
Goal:
Only provisioners group can create projects.
Edit role binding:
oc edit clusterrolebinding self-provisioners
Change:
Group system:authenticated:oauth
to
Group provisioners
Final configuration:
subjects:
- apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
  kind: Group
  name: provisioners
