1пёЏвѓЈ4пёЏвѓЈ Create Project Template
Now we convert this configuration into a Project Template.
Generate template:
oc adm create-bootstrap-project-template -o yaml > template.yaml
This generates default project template.
________________________________________
1пёЏвѓЈ5пёЏвѓЈ Modify Template
We add:
1пёЏвѓЈ Project object
2пёЏвѓЈ RoleBinding
3пёЏвѓЈ LimitRange
Important modification:
Change RoleBinding subject
Default:
User
Change to:
Group provisioners
________________________________________
Add LimitRange
- apiVersion: v1
  kind: LimitRange
  metadata:
    name: max-memory
    namespace: ${PROJECT_NAME}
  spec:
    limits:
    - default:
        memory: 1Gi
      defaultRequest:
        memory: 1Gi
      max:
        memory: 1Gi
      type: Container
Important variable:
${PROJECT_NAME}
OpenShift replaces it automatically when project is created.
________________________________________
1пёЏвѓЈ6пёЏвѓЈ Create Template
Command:
oc create -f template.yaml -n openshift-config
Namespace:
openshift-config
This is where cluster configuration templates are stored.
________________________________________
1пёЏвѓЈ7пёЏвѓЈ Configure Cluster to Use Template
Edit project configuration:
oc edit projects.config.openshift.io cluster
Add:
spec:
  projectRequestTemplate:
    name: project-request
Meaning:
Whenever someone runs:
oc new-project
OpenShift uses this template.
